# UI/UX Rules

## Design System
- **Reference**: `apps/web/DESIGN_SYSTEM.md` — Complete design system documentation
- **Visual Preview**: `/design-system` route — Interactive token showcase
- Use shadcn/ui components from `components/ui/` as foundation
- Follow "Acid Brutalism" aesthetic: hard shadows, bold borders, kinetic accents
- Design tokens defined in `globals.css` and `tailwind.config.ts`

### Color Usage (Acid Brutalism)
| Token | Value | Usage |
|-------|-------|-------|
| `--coral` | #FF6B35 | Primary CTAs (10% usage) |
| `--teal` | #00A896 | Success states (5% usage) |
| `--acid` | #CCFF00 | Kinetic elements (2% usage only) |
| `--electric` | #8B5CF6 | Hover states |
| `--ink` | #09090B | Backgrounds |
| `--paper` | #FAFAFA | Surfaces |

### Typography
- **dela** → Hero headlines (`font-dela`)
- **display** (Geist) → Section headings (`font-display`)
- **sans** → Body text, UI elements
- **mono** → Code, technical content

### Component Patterns
- **One brutalist element per view** — Let it stand out
- Use `cn()` utility for className merging
- Extend shadcn patterns with custom variants
- See `components/ui/button.tsx` for variant examples

## Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)
- Minimum contrast: 4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text
- All interactive elements must be keyboard accessible
- Use semantic HTML elements (main, article, section, nav)
- Include proper ARIA labels for screen readers
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` for animations

## Component Patterns
```tsx
// Always include ARIA attributes
<button
  aria-label="Close modal"
  aria-expanded={isOpen}
  aria-controls="modal-content"
  onClick={onClose}
>
  <X aria-hidden="true" />
</button>
```

## Loading & Error States
- Show loading indicators for async operations
- Provide meaningful error messages
- Include empty states with clear next actions
- Use skeleton loaders for content placeholders

## Forms
- Label all inputs (visible or aria-label)
- Show validation errors inline
- Disable submit during processing
- Provide success feedback

## Responsive Design
- Mobile-first approach
- Test on common breakpoints (sm: 640px, md: 768px, lg: 1024px, xl: 1280px)
- Touch targets minimum 44x44px on mobile

## Performance
- LCP < 2.5s, FID < 100ms, CLS < 0.1
- Lazy load below-fold content
- Optimize images with next/image
- Use CSS transforms for animations (not layout properties)
